{
  "stem": "23350.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Everybody was using it, the Poles, the Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were closed in by fence.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And every, I don't know, every meter or every one and a half meter was one of the Germans with a rifle.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was guarded all the time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They were always changing the guards there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And always, day and night, it's being guarded, the ghetto, so you couldn't get out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to get across the other side, from one side to the other, we had to cross a bridge.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in winter the bridges got so snowed on and iced up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And It was impossible to get across.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had to have the strength to get across to the other side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then I had that really hard life because from there I had to cross another, not a bridge, this time gates where the Germans were standing and wouldn't let you go across until there was about 200 people standing in the cold and the ice in the morning.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we had to arrive on time to the factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Otherwise we didn't get the soup.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We couldn't get in because they wouldn't let you in late in the factory.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was terribly difficult.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But there are two fellows who were with me in the ghetto, in the same factory.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And every time when I came in, we had a thing to give up when we came in in the factory, out of card [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I used to throw it across, and they opened the gate for me and let me in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They felt sorry for me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister worked in a shoe factory.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Slippers-- they used to-- you know, from Auschwitz, from the clothes, which used to come back, they used to make [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] slippers out of it.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
